Paper: hep-th/9503224

Date: 1995-03-31

Title: What's Wrong with Pauli-Villars Regularization in $QED_{3}$ ?

Authors: B. M. Pimentel and J. L. Tomazelli

Comments: 07 pages, Latex, no figures

Journal-ref: Prog.Theor.Phys. 95 (1996) 1217-1222

In this letter we argue that there is no ambiguity between the Pauli-Villarsand other methods of regularization in (2+1)-dimensional quantumelectrodynamics with respect to dynamical mass generation, provided we properlychoose the couplings for the regulators.